did.abstract: Records created or collected by the dean of the College of Health Sciences (formerly the School of Allied Health Professions), containing brochures and bulletins; correspondence; faculty meeting minutes; various committee files, including miscellaneous search and screen committee records; and teaching evaluation summaries. The records largely document course and curriculum development, including the development of a bachelor of science in allied health and several master's and PhD programs; staffing, budget, and space needs; and committee activities. Information about the departments within the school can also be found in the collection, particularly in the correspondence, minutes, and curriculum files. The collection also contains unclassified personnel records which are restricted.

bioghist.p: The School of Allied Health Professions was established in August 1975. In 2001, the name of the school was changed to the College of Health Sciences.

scopecontent.p: Materials from the various offices and departments of the College of Health Sciences. The majority of the collection consists of departmental meeting minutes and subject files from the constituent departments of the College of Health Sciences: the Dept. of Clinical Laboratory Sciences; the Dept. of Communication Sciences and Disorders; the Dept. of Health Sciences; the Dept. of Human Kinetics, including the Kinesiology program; the Dept. of Speech Pathology and Audiology; the Health Information Administration Program (later renamed the Department of Healthcare Administration and Informatics); the Health Career Opportunity Program; the J. Martin Klotsche Center for Physical Education; the Medical Technology Program; and the Dept. of Occupational Therapy. Most of the files within these departments deal with the addition of new courses or degree programs. Also included are numerous files related to the accreditation process for programs, departments, and the entire college.

The general files of the School include materials on special projects and relationships maintained by the Dean's Office, including Allied Health Week, affiliation agreements with public health institutions in Milwaukee, information on remodeling of Enderis and Lapham halls, and files on the School's participation in the Milwaukee Initiative and Milwaukee Idea. Of particular interest are files on the establishment of a collaborative physical therapy program with UW-La Crosse, as well as a large number of files on the budget and program priorities of the College. The College of Health Sciences was responsible for much of the planning of UWM's School of Public Health, and planning for that new campus unit is reflected in the collection. Also included are yearly planning documents, UWM internal reviews of the College as a whole, grant information, and information on credit and curriculum changes.
Box 7 was noted as missing on February 20, 2009. An inventory of the folders in this box is available in the collection case file. Ask an archivist for more information.

arrangement.p: This collection was received in, and is organized in, multiple parts. Additional materials have not been physically or intellectually arranged and interfiled, and researchers may need to consult more than one part of the collection to locate similar materials.
The collection contains seven additional accessions.

accessrestrict.p: The unclassified personnel files in boxes 3-11, 16, and 35 as well as accessions 1998-048 (box 2), 2002-075, 2003-047, 2007-016, 2010-003, 2016-010, and boxes 3-4 of 2001-014 are restricted in accordance with UWM Personnel File Policy S-42. Access is regulated by Section III.A.2 and III.A.3. Additional folders in box 19 are restricted in accordance with the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act on 1973 (FERPA).
There are no access restrictions on the rest of the collection, which is open to all members of the public in accordance with state law.

userestrict.p: The researcher assumes full responsibility for conforming with the laws of libel, privacy, and copyright which may be involved in the use of this collection (Wisconsin Statutes 19.21-19.39).

acqinfo.p: An unknown individual transferred the collection to the Archives prior to 1989. Kristene Lindert transferred materials in January 1998 (accession 1998-048). Patti Sander donated additional material in October 2001 (accession 2001-014). The College of Health Sciences transferred accessions 2011-049 and 2012-005 to the Archives in June-July 2012. The College of Health Sciences transferred electronic photos (accession 2013-002) in July 2013 and additional records (accession 2016-010) in August 2016.

processinfo.p: Christel T. Maass reprocessed the collection at the Archives in December 1993. Hayley Jackson updated the finding aid to include information about accession 1998-048 in October 2013. Hayley Jackson updated the finding aid to include information about accession 2001-014 in November 2014. Brad Houston and Charlie Tonelli processed accessions 2011-049 and 2012-005 over Winter 2015. Ashlie Biddle processed the non-restricted portions of accessions 2002-075 and 2003-047 in April 2016 (Brad Houston supervised). Brad Houston added information about accession 2016-010 and processed accession 2013-002 and the electronic portion of accession 2011-049 in October 2016.

scopecontent.p: Minutes for College-wide Faculty and Staff meetings, as well as departmental committee meeting minutes for the Health Sciences Department, the Department of Communication Sciences and Disorders, and the Department of Human Kinetics. Also included are program evaluations for the Human Kinetics graduate and undergraduate programs.
